By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Senate President, Ahmad Lawan on Tuesday lamented of excessive heat inside the Senate chambers arising from faulty cooling system. Lawan who made the observation during plenary, directed the Clerk to the Senate to ensure that the cooling system of the chambers is put right as soon as possible. According to the Senate President, “This chamber appears unduly warm this morning. We can’t be battling with debate and fanning ourselves. I want to appeal to our colleagues to be patient as the fault would be fixed soonest,” Lawan said. Sundiata Post gathered that the heat was caused by malfunctioning of the cooling system in the chambers. He however added that technicians in the National Assembly were working to rectify the anomaly. 